On this Pakistani Independence Day, we are raising funds for @tcfusa in their efforts to educate underprivileged children in Pakistan, and we would love your support. #runforeducation #tcfusa #changebeginswitheducation

Pakistan has over 22 million children outside of the education system. TCF (The Citizen’s Foundation) was founded 28 years ago to fight this crisis, and today it operates and owns 2000 schools in Pakistan aiming to provide a high standard of education to children in underserved areas. 

Not only is TCF educating 280,000 children in Pakistan, it is also committed to supporting and empowering women. With exclusively female faculties, it is the largest private employer of women in Pakistan, and ensures that all schools have a 50:50 boy / girl ratio.

Please donate any amount you are able to through the link in my bio, or go to https://fundraise.tcfglobal.org/fundraiser/408783459240/bake-with-zoha-x-tcf 💚 Every little contribution makes a big difference!

One thing about me is that I am a perfectionist and love to hold myself to extremely high standards, and then be hard on myself 🤷🏻‍♀️ 

For instance, I’ve always found food photography challenging. It is way more nuanced and involved than you would think: you have to make the food in a way that not only tastes good but also looks good on camera, you have to style the scene and bring together the serverware, props, textures and colors in a way that doesn’t look bland but still allows the food to stand out, you have to think about lighting and shadows, work the right camera angles, and edit in a way that makes thing look natural and not staged. Easy, right? 🤯

Seriously - when I started doing this, I just couldn’t get the hang of it and wondered why i found it so hard. And I still struggle with it - I keep thinking I suck at it and have a lot to learn. 

But the beauty of being a content creator is that I can see my growth over time. I was scrolling back and found some food pictures from when I first started last year (swipe to see them, and mind you - these were my best attempts), and felt completely shocked. It’s so easy for me to get sucked into future goals and focus on what I’m lacking that I forget how far I’ve come. And I have come a really long way, and I am really proud of myself. Especially considering all these pictures are taken from an iPhone 🥲

So why am I sharing this? It’s not to pat myself on my back. It’s because I’m sure many of you need this reminder. I’m sure many of you also tend to stress about what’s next and forget to just be present. And I want you to take a moment to reflect right now. Think about where you were a year or two ago - the things you wished to accomplish, the goals you wanted to meet. And then think about how far you’ve come since then, how much you have achieved and learned and grown. And just be proud of yourself, celebrate yourself, and give yourself grace and compassion. As Kris Jenner would put it, “you’re doing great, sweetie” ❤️

Someone pinch me. I can’t believe I got to shoot a recipe on set with @delish in NYC and now have a feature on their website! Like, hello, is this still real life? 🥹

I remember being a kid baking or cooking in the kitchen and secretly pretending that I was doing a cooking show, talking to an imaginary camera. I never told anyone, never thought it could ever become reality. And not that I have a cooking show now, but this day came pretty close to feeling like it 🥲 I got to work with a phenomenal team ranging from hair and make up to wardrobe to food producers, recipe developers, prop stylists, and a whole camera and audio crew. Everyone treated me so kindly and allowed me to be myself and share who I am, where I come from, and create a recipe I love. It honestly felt so surreal - I was having an out of body experience the entire time. 

I’m just so utterly grateful to the team @delish and to you guys. and hope this is just the beginning for us ❤️ Alhamdulillah 

You can find my recipe for Salted Caramel No Bake Cheesecakes featuring @werthersoriginalus now on delish.com! And also a teeny little article about me. I’ll link both in my bio ☺️

Today I want to speak to those of you who are still confused, and don’t understand why millions around the world are siding with Palestine. Who have been led to believe this is too complicated to have an opinion. It is not complicated, and it is not too late to demand an end to a cycle of violence that has led to the loss of thousands of innocent lives and the displacement of millions. In fact, it is our collective moral responsibility to do so.

I want to share a few incredible resources with you and sincerely hope you will check them out. All of these are available on YouTube:

1. The Danger Of Neutrality - a Ted Talk by Anna Baltzer, a Jewish American author and activist 

2. Gaza Fights For Freedom - an incredible documentary by Abby Martin @empirefiles which covers the Great March Of Return - a nonviolent protest led by the people of Gaza in 2018-19 who wanted to be let back into their land, and were brutalized by Israeli forces. This documentary provides a rich perspective on the 75 year history of occupation and colonization, and shows the stark contrast between reality and what is portrayed in western media.

3. Life In Occupied Palestine - this is a simple one hour long documentary from 9 years ago in which Anna shares what life is like for Palestinians living under Israeli occupation based on her own experience. Things have only gotten worse since then

4. Abby Martin’s (@fababs) interviews with Joe Rogan talking about the reality of the horrors faced by Palestinians on a daily basis. I highly recommend following all content from @fababs and @empirefiles which cover this topic in depth 

Artwork by @ayaillustrates . These are just 2 of the 4000+ innocent children who have been killed in the past month.

Go to ceasefiretoday.com and join me in demanding a ceasefire today.

Let’s make 3 incredible Thanksgiving desserts in under 2 hours with the help of @amazonfresh ! 🤤 #ad 

▫️Scrumptious Cinnamon Roll Monkey Bread 
▫️Decadent Chocolate Cheesecake Cake 
▫️Mouthwatering Apple Crumble Pie 

I really think Amazon Fresh stores are the future of grocery shopping, and if you haven’t visited one, you have to! You can scan items as you go using the Dash Cart, ask Alexa kiosks where to find things, and then simply walk out of the store when you’re done shopping. No need to wait in long check out lines 🤯 So if you’re preparing for the Holidays, visit your closest Amazon Fresh store or get everything delivered, and save this video for tips and tricks to simplify desserts ❤️

Cinnamon Roll Monkey Bread: 
● 2 cans buttermilk biscuits 
● 1/2 cup sugar 
● 1 Tbsp cinnamon 
● 3/4 cup butter 
● 1/2 cup brown sugar 
● Bake at 350F for ~30 min in a bundt pan 

Chocolate Cheesecake Cake: 
● 1 box chocolate cake mix 
● 3/4 cup hot coffee 
● 1/2 Cup oil 
● 3 Eggs 
● 1/4 cup sour cream 
● Bake at 350F for 25 min in a 9x13” pan 
● Frosting: 1 pack cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1 pack cool whip 

Apple Crumble Pie: 
● 1 9” pie crust 
● 2 cans apple pie filling 
● 1 cup flour 
● 1/2 cup sugar 
● 1⁄2 teaspoon cinnamon 
● 1⁄2 tsp salt 
● 6 tbsp butter 
● Bake at 375F for ~40-50 min, covering with foil up in the last 15 min to prevent burning

A heartfelt love letter from me to you. 

We know this past month and a half have been difficult for many, and in this time I made the decision to not just post food content but also use my platform to raise my voice about a cause I care about. This is always a daunting thing to do as a creator since cancel culture is rampant, but you guys have made me feel incredibly supported. I know hate often gets more attention, but the truth is 99% of all messages and comments I’ve gotten have been nothing but positive, respectful and compassionate. 

So I want to take a moment and thank you all. Not for agreeing with me, but for allowing me to be a full human being. For making me feel safe. For making me feel loved and heard. For respecting my identity. For giving me the benefit of doubt and trusting my intention.

I have said this before and I will say it again: I cherish you all and I cherish this community. I hope to always be a source of positivity in your lives. I hope to always uphold my responsibility as a creator with a platform. I know I won’t be perfect, I know there will be many instances where we disagree, but I hope we can always be kind, compassionate and forgiving above all else. And last but not the least, I hope to always fill your feed with delicious food.

Much love to all of you, regardless of who you are or where you’re from. If you’re hurting, I feel your pain. If you’re happy, I feel your joy. I cherish you and am grateful for you. ❤️🥹
